    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>The EEE classroom is quite an explosive class. The explosiveness depends on the type and number of students present in the class. Specifically, the explosiveness doubles every time a new person enters the class and finds at least one member of his gang already present in the class.  </p>\n<p>\u00a0Given the details of the class gangs, print the minimum possible explosiveness of the class mod 1000000007.\n</p>\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<p>The first line of the input contains two integers, <b>N</b> the number of students present in the class and <b>M</b> . The next <b>M</b> lines contain 2 integers <b>A</b> and <b>B</b> such that student number (<b>A</b> and student number <b>B</b> belong to the same gang.</p>\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>Print the minimum possible explosiveness of the class mod <b>1000000007</b> by optimizing the entry sequence of the students. The initial explosiveness of the class is <b> 1 </b>. Only one student enters the class at a time and all the n students must attend the class (Attendance shortage is a big issue here).</p>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>N</b> \u2264 <b>1000000</b></li>\n<li><b>0</b> \u2264 <b>M</b> \u2264 <b>(N*(N-1))/2</b></li>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>A, B</b> \u2264 <b>N</b></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n5 3\n1 2\n2 3\n5 4\n<b>Output:</b>\n8\n</pre><h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example case 1.</b><br />\n Let the entry sequence be 5 1 2 3 4.<br />\nWhen 5 enters the class, the explosiveness doesn't change.<br />\nSame is the case with 1 as no member of his gang is present.<br />\n2 enters and finds 1 so the explosiveness doubles to 1*2 = 2.<br />\n3 doubles it again to 2*2 = 4.<br />\nFinally 4 enters and finds 5 so the explosiveness doubles again to 2*4 = 8.<br />\nTherefore the answer is 8 % 1000000007 = 8.\n</p>\n",
